## üí° **Example Use Case**

A driver in downtown Chicago exceeds the 35 mph speed limit on a slippery road.
RSIS immediately announces:

> ‚ÄúSpeed limit 35. Road surface icy ‚Äî reduce to 25 mph. Two recent accidents in this area.‚Äù

The vehicle dashboard flashes an amber warning, GPS reroutes to safer roads, and the driver‚Äôs score reflects a ‚Äúspeed warning issued.‚Äù
Over time, the system notices many incidents here and sends feedback to city planners:

> ‚ÄúHigh rate of loss-of-control at 5th and Lake ‚Äî suggest traction resurfacing.‚Äù

